71a378ff978714d3d988","sha":"a093eb47f75dd26ad0f771a378ff978714d3d988","node_id":"MDY6Q29tbWl0MTAyNDU1NDI2NzphMDkzZWI0N2Y3NWRkMjZhZDBmNzcxYTM3OGZmOTc4NzE0ZDNkOTg4","html_url":"https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/commit/a093eb47f75dd26ad0f771a378ff978714d3d988","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/NousResearch/hermes-agent/commits/a093eb47f75dd26ad0f771a378ff978714d3d988/comments","commit":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/NousResearch/hermes-agent/git/commits/a093eb47f75dd26ad0f771a378ff978714d3d988","author":{"date":"2026-04-10T12:51:30.000-07:00","name":"Teknium","email":"127238744+teknium1@users.noreply.github.com"},"committer":{"date":"2026-04-10T12:51:30.000-07:00","name":"GitHub","email":"noreply@github.com"},"message":"fix: propagate child activity to parent during delegate_task (#7295)\n\nWhen delegate_task runs, the parent agent's activity tracker freezes\nbecause child.run_conversation() blocks and the child's own\n_touch_activity() never propagates back to the parent. The gateway\ninactivity timeout then fires a spurious 'No activity' warning and\neventually kills the agent, even though the subagent is actively working.\n\nFix: add a heartbeat thread in _run_single_child that calls\nparent._touch_activity() every 30 seconds with detail from the child's\nactivity summary (current tool, iteration count). The thread is a daemon\nthat starts before child.run_conversation() and is cleaned up in the\nfinally block.\n\nThis also improves the gateway 'Still working...' status messages —\ninstead of just 'running: delegate_task', users now see what the\nsubagent is actually doing (e.g., 'delegate_task: subagent running\nterminal (iteration 5/50)').","tree":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/NousResearch/hermes-agent/git/trees/49f8a359f80eb1ff25dc5db26b60ddcca66366aa","sha":"49f8a359f80eb1ff25dc5db26b60ddcca66366aa"},"comment_count":0},"author":{"login":"teknium1","id":127238744,"node_id":"U_kgDOB5WCWA","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubuser